The paper deals with a graph optimization problem (Steiner Point Removal) and uses techniques from metric decomposition and probability theory. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the distortion of shortest-path distances, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
